                <head>97. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On September 24 Secretary <persName corresp="#p_HCAJ1">Herter</persName> and
                    Under Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DCD1">Dillon</persName> met with Foreign
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_FA8">Fujiyama</persName> and Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_AK5">Asakai</persName> in Washington. Assistant Secretary of
                    Defense <persName corresp="#p_IJNII1">Irwin</persName> also participated in the
                    meeting, at which there was general discussion of the security treaty
                    negotiations, the current international situation, <gloss target="#t_GARIOA1"
                        >GARIOA</gloss>, trade issues, and the Algerian situation. Text of the
                    memorandum of conversation by <persName corresp="#p_SRL2">Richard L.
                        Sneider</persName>, Officer in Charge of Japanese Affairs, is in the
                    Supplement.</p>
            </div>
